returns.description:
"false".

	* Return type: The function returns a boolean value, which means it can take on only two values - true or false.
	* Value: The function always returns false. This means that the output of the function is always the same, regardless of any input provided to the function.
	* Scope: The function has no scope as it is defined inside an IIFE (Immediately Invoked Function Expression) and does not access any external variables or functions.
